Company history[edit]


The early days
1996
REC established in Norway


1997
First wafer washed by hand in summer 1997


Industrialization
1997-2010
Production of wafers, solar cells, and solar panels in Scandinavia (Norway and Sweden)


Growth phase
2010
Fully automated and integrated production of wafers, cells, and panels begins at state-of-the-art factory in Singapore


2013
Split of REC Group from Renewable Energy Corporation ASA (now known as “REC Silicon ASA”)


2015
REC acquired by Norway’s Elkem Group and is delisted from the Oslo Stock Exchange


